      <h2>Signs Your Dryer Vent Needs Repair</h2>
      <p>
        &bull; Long Drying Times: If your clothes are taking longer than usual
        to dry, it could indicate a clogged or damaged vent.<br /><br />
        &bull; Excessive Lint Buildup: Check your lint trap and dryer area for excessive
        lint accumulation, which can obstruct airflow.<br /><br />
        &bull; Hot Dryer Exterior: An overheating dryer exterior or a burning smell
        during operation signals potential vent issues.<br /><br />
        &bull; Visible Damage: Look for visible signs of vent damage, such as crushed
        or disconnected sections.
      </p>

      <h2>Our Repair Process</h2>
      <p>
        &bull; Assessment: Our technicians conduct a thorough assessment to
